# Common Network Ports

| Port | Protocol | Service |
|-------|----------|----------|
|20|TCP|FTP Data|
|21|TCP|FTP Control|
|22|TCP|SSH|
|23|TCP|Telnet|
|25|TCP|SMTP|
|53|TCP/UDP|DNS|
|67|UDP|DHCP|
|68|UDP|DHCP Client|
|80|TCP|HTTP|
|110|TCP|POP3|
|143|TCP|IMAP|
|443|TCP|HTTPS|
|3389|TCP|RDP|

---

## Key Takeaways

Ports identify applications running on a device.

Multiple applications can communicate simultaneously because each uses different port numbers.
